# Responsive design tokens — additions to `src/app/globals.css`

Merge the following into the existing `@theme` block. The fluid type, fluid
spacing, and touch tokens are required by every project that runs
`add-responsive-foundation`.

## What to add inside `@theme`

```css
@theme {
  /* ============================================================== */
  /* Fluid type scale — clamp() based.                              */
  /* Min value (mobile) → max value (desktop), smooth interpolation. */
  /* Numbers tuned for: minimum 360px viewport → maximum 1536px.    */
  /* ============================================================== */
  --text-fluid-xs: clamp(0.75rem, 0.7rem + 0.25vw, 0.875rem);     /* 12 → 14 */
  --text-fluid-sm: clamp(0.875rem, 0.825rem + 0.25vw, 1rem);      /* 14 → 16 */
  --text-fluid-base: clamp(1rem, 0.95rem + 0.25vw, 1.125rem);     /* 16 → 18 */
  --text-fluid-lg: clamp(1.125rem, 1.05rem + 0.4vw, 1.375rem);    /* 18 → 22 */
  --text-fluid-xl: clamp(1.25rem, 1.15rem + 0.5vw, 1.75rem);      /* 20 → 28 */
  --text-fluid-2xl: clamp(1.5rem, 1.35rem + 0.75vw, 2.25rem);     /* 24 → 36 */
  --text-fluid-3xl: clamp(1.875rem, 1.65rem + 1.25vw, 3rem);      /* 30 → 48 */
  --text-fluid-4xl: clamp(2.5rem, 2.1rem + 2vw, 4rem);            /* 40 → 64 */
  --text-fluid-5xl: clamp(3rem, 2.4rem + 3vw, 5rem);              /* 48 → 80 */

  /* ============================================================== */
  /* Fluid spacing scale — section gaps that scale with viewport.   */
  /* For component-internal spacing, use Tailwind's static scale.   */
  /* For page sections / hero / between-major-blocks, use these.    */
  /* ============================================================== */
  --space-fluid-2xs: clamp(0.5rem, 0.45rem + 0.25vw, 0.75rem);    /*  8 → 12 */
  --space-fluid-xs: clamp(0.75rem, 0.65rem + 0.5vw, 1rem);        /* 12 → 16 */
  --space-fluid-sm: clamp(1rem, 0.85rem + 0.75vw, 1.5rem);        /* 16 → 24 */
  --space-fluid-md: clamp(1.5rem, 1.25rem + 1.25vw, 2.5rem);      /* 24 → 40 */
  --space-fluid-lg: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 2.5vw, 4rem);            /* 32 → 64 */
  --space-fluid-xl: clamp(3rem, 2.25rem + 3.75vw, 6rem);          /* 48 → 96 */
  --space-fluid-2xl: clamp(4rem, 3rem + 5vw, 8rem);               /* 64 → 128 */

  /* ============================================================== */
  /* Touch targets — WCAG 2.2 AA minimum is 44×44 (target 2.5.8).   */
  /* `touch-lg` is the Material Design / preferred 48×48.            */
  /* ============================================================== */
  --size-touch: 2.75rem;         /* 44px */
  --size-touch-lg: 3rem;         /* 48px */

  /* ============================================================== */
  /* Container max-widths — the locked page-content widths.         */
  /* ResponsiveContainer uses these.                                 */
  /* ============================================================== */
  --container-narrow: 720px;     /* article reading width */
  --container-default: 1280px;   /* default app shell content width */
  --container-wide: 1536px;      /* dashboards, data-heavy layouts */
}
```

## Container-query setup

Tailwind 4 supports container queries natively via `@container`. No plugin needed.
Use as:

```html
<div class="@container">
  <h2 class="@md:text-fluid-2xl text-fluid-xl">Adapts to parent width</h2>
</div>
```

## Print stylesheet (optional but recommended)

Append at the end of `globals.css` (outside `@theme`):

```css
@media print {
  /* Hide non-content chrome */
  nav, header, footer, aside, [data-no-print] { display: none !important; }

  /* Black on white for ink savings */
  body { background: white !important; color: black !important; }

  /* Avoid breaking inside headings */
  h1, h2, h3 { break-after: avoid; }

  /* Don't break images / tables across pages */
  img, table { break-inside: avoid; }

  /* Show URLs for printed links */
  a[href]::after {
    content: " (" attr(href) ")";
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: #555;
  }
}
```

## Reduced motion (already in add-accessibility, but reaffirmed here)

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    scroll-behavior: auto !important;
  }
}
```
